Author Response: Thank you for the suggested references; we incorporated some of them into the manuscript. The allotment movement popular both within the ex-Communist and western Europe must be mentioned, e.g. Klepacki, P. and Kujawska, M., 2018. Urban allotment gardens in Poland: Implications for botanical and landscape diversity. This paper is a report from a project done in 2009-2012 by the Ethnographic Museum in Kraków documenting the importance of allotments in Poland, both in a cultural and biological context. Sowińska-Świerkosz, B., Michalik-Śnieżek, M. and Bieske-Matejak, A., 2021. Can Allotment Gardens (AGs) Be Considered an Example of Nature-Based Solutions (NBS) Based on the Use of Historical Green Infrastructure? (

    https://doi.org/10.3390/su13020835
) The expressions ‘organic farming’ and ‘permaculture’ are not mentioned in the paper, and they are important part of the food security discussion. Thank you for the suggested references; we have expanded a bit the discussion on this subject and incorporated them into the text.
